        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer337422" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13080625157186400319">While I enjoyed Dunant&apos;s first novel, <i>The Birth of Venus</i> moreso than this work, I think she has a great knack for writing extremely interesting characters. Bucino is a great hero for her novel and she also does a wonderful job of characterizing 16th century Venice as well. <br/><br/>The novel started off quickly, however the middle moved VERY slowly and made the ending less exciting. I was hoping for more of a resolution, and more exposition, but in the end the book doesn&apos;t really need to provide the read</span>
  <span id="freeText13080625157186400319" style="display:none">While I enjoyed Dunant's first novel, <i>The Birth of Venus</i> moreso than this work, I think she has a great knack for writing extremely interesting characters. Bucino is a great hero for her novel and she also does a wonderful job of characterizing 16th century Venice as well. <br /><br />The novel started off quickly, however the middle moved VERY slowly and made the ending less exciting. I was hoping for more of a resolution, and more exposition, but in the end the book doesn't really need to provide the reader with a concrete conclusion. <br /><br />I'd love to see this made into a film. I think Peter Dinklage would make an astounding Bucino - hopefully someone will option the book and do right by the source material. <br /><br /></span>
